	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: M82 replica help</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This is going to be much more obnoxious and probably more expensive than you want it to be, although you'll find some things are a little cheaper (parts) and some things are a lot more expensive (PCB) if you actually build a 12-up device.<br /><br />It sounds like you already read <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9122" class="postlink">this thread</a>?<br /><br />Extending the concept to a 1-of-N device is straightforward, but won't have to use the same parts; you might find the 74'138/'238 (8 or 16 up) / '139/'239 (4 up) sometimes useful.<br /><br />Using a pushbutton to rotate between cartridges would probably be best done with with an analog debounce circuit on the button and a counter like a 74'161; other options may be better depending on specifics.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


