_circuits" class="postlink">7400</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_4000_series_integrated_circuits" class="postlink">4000</a> family for seven- or 7- segment)</div><br /><br />- I looked into the other chips and I have found the appropriate set of chips to enable the circuit to count and display (from my local electronics retailer), but I have a few more questions about chip functionality, for instance to send a signal to the rest of the circuit ie. enable a set of IC's that control the disconnected portions of each 72 pin. what would I use, would I use the output of the 7 segment or the output of the connectors from the decade counter/ synchronous counter?<br /><br />- I apologize for any garbled sentences -

		

